body_html:
We have updated the retrain tutorials to use hub which should resolved some model issues with deciding what models to use. https://github.com/tensorflow/hub/blob/master/examples/image_retraining/retrain.py

That being said, i think the issue is that the retrain script is somehow picking up an old quantized model that uses TF dequantization operations (which doesn't actually fully quantize the model)

i think you should specify mobilenet_1.0_224_quant instead of mobilenet_1.0_224_quantized

Apologies for the confusion.

body:
We have updated the retrain tutorials to use hub which should resolved some model issues with deciding what models to use. https://github.com/tensorflow/hub/blob/master/examples/image_retraining/retrain.py 

That being said, i think the issue is that the retrain script is somehow picking up an old quantized model that uses TF dequantization operations (which doesn't actually fully quantize the model)

i think you should specify `mobilenet_1.0_224_quant` instead of `mobilenet_1.0_224_quantized`

Apologies for the confusion.
